benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/resume - Resume a bundle

covered: Valid Request: TC01 demonstrates a successful resume with 204 and state transition to active.
Non-Existing Resource: TC05 covers 404 when bundle is not found.
Invalid BundleId format: TC06 covers 400 for malformed bundleId.
Missing required header: TC07 covers 400 when X-Killbill-CreatedBy header is missing.
Authorization: TC10 covers 401/403 for invalid token.
Query Parameters coverage: TC02, TC03, TC04 validate requestedDate, pluginProperty and combined optional params.
Partial Update: TC18 demonstrates resuming with only required fields.
Concurrency: TC21 demonstrates handling of concurrent requests.
Server Error Handling: TC14 demonstrates 500 internal server error when a dependency is unavailable.
Server Error Handling: TC25 demonstrates 504 when a dependent service times out or is degraded.
Edge/Validation: TC19 handles invalid pluginProperty format (non-array).
Edge/Validation: TC20 handles requestedDate in the past as invalid.
Security: TC16 handles SQL injection attempts in pluginProperty.
Security: TC17 handles XSS attempt in X-Killbill-Comment header.
Backward compatibility: TC24 covers legacy client headers.
Large Payloads: TC13 tests behavior with a very large number of pluginProperty values.
Extra/unexpected parameters: TC11 covers extra parameters being ignored or accepted.
Maximum header length: TC12 verifies handling of maximum length header values.
Whitespace/case variations in headers: TC26 ensures normalization of header values.
Retry/Transient failures: TC15 demonstrates retry logic on transient failures.
Performance: TC22 checks response time under normal and peak load.
Regression: TC23 covers previously fixed edge cases.
Integration: TC25 validates behavior when plugin service experiences latency (latency tolerance or fallback).
Audit/logging: TC04 scenario confirms audit-related recording of reason/comment.
gaps: Rate limiting and throttling tests (expected 429 on bursts) are not covered.
Caching behavior tests (ETag/Cache-Control) are not covered for the PUT endpoint.
Explicit empty-body validation for 204 responses (beyond assuming empty body) is not separately asserted.
Duplicate submission/idempotency tests (re-sending identical PUT) are not covered.
Pagination tests are not applicable to this endpoint and not explicitly covered (not a gap per se, but noted as not needed).
Additional cross-bundle or multi-resource concurrency scenarios are not covered (only single bundle concurrency).
recommendations: Add a rate-limiting test to verify proper 429 responses under high-frequency or bursty PUT requests to /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/resume.
Add caching header validation tests for this PUT endpoint (ETag/Cache-Control) to ensure correct caching semantics where applicable.
Introduce an explicit test asserting the PUT response body is empty for 204 (confirm no body content).
Add idempotency/duplicate submission tests to ensure repeated identical PUT requests do not cause inconsistent state or errors.
Where applicable, add additional concurrency scenarios across multiple bundles to exercise broader locking/consistency behavior.
Document and test edge cases around extremely long or unusual header values to ensure robust normalization beyond whitespace variations.
Consider explicit tests for network timeouts causing retries or fallback behavior beyond the existing TC15 and TC25.
If applicable, add a brief regression test for any newly discovered edge case not yet covered (beyond TC23).
